    <Room>
      <VNum>4456</VNum>
      <Name>A beautiful alcove.</Name>
      <Description>You stand in a small, magnificent alcove. The plants and animals around
you are stunning and breathtaking. Hundreds of small birds and soft, calm
animals roam the alcove bathing in the golden sun. On the northwestern
portion of the alcove is a tall shady tree; under it is a beautiful elven
harpist. The entire alcove is filled with sweet and flagrant music. The
small trail heads back towards where you entered. - On the ground is a small
stone slab with writing etched into it.</Description>
      <Sector>Forest</Sector>
      <Flags>NoMob</Flags>
      <Exits />
      <ExtraDescriptions>
        <ExtraDescription>
          <Keyword>slab floor stone</Keyword>
          <Description>-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
= The Sarn Athrael = - - = Translating into modern text the Sarn Athrael
would simply mean = - "The Stone Athrael". Of course behind all great
treasures there - = is a tale of beauty and love, courage and deceit, and
the honor = - of ones virtues and desires. Unfortunately, that is a tale you
- = shall not hear this day, but another day. For today all you must = -
understand is the Sarn Athrael stands for beauty, Respect, and - =
Knowledge. Seek the Divine Lord valinor if you understand those = - words I
speak. - = =
-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-</Description>
        </ExtraDescription>
      </ExtraDescriptions>
